race.comment: DAPHNES (6) is a promising filly back from a 36-week spell. Ran Tempted to a long neck on debut over 1000m. Last raced when a respectable third over 1300m at Newcastle. Two recent trials should have her right up to the mark. NAMASTE (1) returns from a five-month spell. Struck wet tracks all of last prep and it didn't help his cause. Raced here twice last summer and was beaten a long neck on each occasion. Recent trial winner who looks set for a positive return. Big market watch on debutant LONTRICE (5) from the Hawkes camp who has won a couple of recent Rosehill trials in good style. SANT GERVASI (9) needs this sort of trip now and can build on his two strong efforts at the provincials to launch his career.
